<h1>Digipalvelutehdas test account for Kielihack</h1>

We have created a dedicated, temporary environment for Kielihack for deploying your web applications on a modern
containerized platform.

<h2>Test account</h2>

<p>
    Here are your test account details:
</p>
<div class="credentials">
    <pre>

    username: {{ username }}
    password: {{ password }}
    </pre>
</div>

<h2>Resources</h2>
<p>
    The platform UI is available at
</p>
<div class="linkblock">
    https://eduhack.digipalvelutehdas.fi:8443
</div>

<p>
    This test account has been granted with a quota of
</p>
<ul>
    <li>2 projects</li>
    <li>each project with
        <ul>
            <li>8 containers, max 1 core and 1GB RAM each</li>
            <li>2 persistent volumes</li>
        </ul>
    </li>
</ul>
<p>
    Your applications will be accessed with HTTP/HTTPS through APP_NAME.eduhack.digipalvelutehdas.fi
</p>

<p>
    If the default set of resources is not sufficient for your use case, please come and ask for more!
</p>
<p>
    For more technical information about the platform, see Pointers -section below.
</p>

<h2>Rules</h2>
<p>
    Please read the following short list of rules:
</p>
<ul>
    <li>The platform is open the to whole internet, so take care in deploying your applications</li>
    <li>No sensitive data should be placed on the platform</li>
    <li>Consider other users of the platform</li>
    <li>The Kielihack environment is deleted after the event</li>
</ul>
<p>
    By using the platform you indicate that you have read and understood the rules above.
</p>

<h2>Pointers</h2>

<p>
    For further information on how to get started, check
</p>

<div class="linkblock">
    https://github.com/tourunen/kielihack2017
</div>
<p>
    Happy Hacking!
</p>

<div class="thanks">
    Thanks for trying out Digipalvelutehdas platform! Please give us feedback during the event!
</div>

